reviews.text: Just one floor below the terrace you had eaten with a great view. Not all tables have this view but there is also an outdoor terrace where you can enjoy the panorama or have a drink. Good food, medium quality pizza, friendly staff.

Pop by here after an afternoon hike. Overall, it is a decent place. I’d give it a 3.5 star if I could. The staff were generally nice. One particular girl was really friendly and her service was top notch. The food is decent. I loved the cream of mushroom. I was not entirely a fan of the fish tacos. I have had better ones. I think you’d come here for the views and it was a clear day with high visibility when I visited, so it was really nice. My only beef with this place is they don’t clear dirty plates quickly so you see lotsa dirty plates left on the tables. It is rather unpleasant and distracting when you’re trying to eat and enjoy the view at the same time.

First, negative points:
Too expensive for what it is.
Pizza is not Italian pizza.

Positive:
It is a pleasure to eat here thanks to the wonderful view on the city of Hong Kong. 
Barramundi fish was really good. 
Tasty light home beer.
Private toilet (no need to stay in a long line in the city mall)
Nice casual dining place...loved their quesadilla. The best part about the place is the spectacular views of the Hong Kong skyline it offers. Best to go there at night.
Reasonable price at the peak where u can see the view as well through the restaurants window! N the food is good!
